body:
#### Issue details
To rename a file I use

`FileHandle#moveTo(FileHandle dest)`

It works fine in most cases. But when I try to rename, for example, a file "abc" to "ABC", the file gets deleted. I think the problem is that file names are insensitve ( at least on Desktop, Windows). This is the implementation of the method mentioned above (I left commentaries in the code):

```
public void moveTo (FileHandle dest) {
    if (type == FileType.Classpath) throw new GdxRuntimeException("Cannot move a classpath file: " + file);
    if (type == FileType.Internal) throw new GdxRuntimeException("Cannot move an internal file: " + file);
    copyTo(dest); // file is not copied into another file, since "abc" file  is the same as the dest "ABC" file
    delete(); // and here the "original" file is deleted, but in this case original file equals to dest file, so the file is lost
    if (exists() && isDirectory()) deleteDirectory();
}
```
**1)** Why there is no `rename `method in FileHandle? Why non-existing method mentioned in [libGDX Wiki](https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/wiki/File-handling#deleting-copying-renaming-and-moving-filesdirectories)?
`Gdx.files.external("myexternalcopy.txt").rename("mycopy.txt");`
**2)** Is it ok to do renaming like this (it works in this case, but maybe there are another caveats):
```
FileHandle src = Gdx.files.local("abc");
src.writeString("some string", false);
FileHandle dest = Gdx.files.local("ABC");
src.file().renameTo(dest.file());
```
It works, even though the [docs of file() method](https://libgdx.badlogicgames.com/nightlies/docs/api/com/badlogic/gdx/files/FileHandle.html#file--) say 

> Note the returned file will only be usable for Files.FileType.Absolute and Files.FileType.External file handles.

which cunfuses me too.

**3)** I think that `moveTo` method could first check, if src and dest are the same file, and in that case don't do anything (or just renaming), instead of deleting. 

#### Reproduction steps/code
```
public class MyGdxGame extends ApplicationAdapter {

    FileHandle src;
    FileHandle dest;

    @Override
    public void create() {
        src = Gdx.files.local("abc");
        src.writeString("some string", false); // creates the file
        dest = Gdx.files.local("ABC");
    }

    @Override
    public void render() {
       //press enter
        if (Gdx.input.isKeyJustPressed(Input.Keys.ENTER)) {
            src.moveTo(dest); // deletes the file
        }
    }
}
```

#### Version of LibGDX and/or relevant dependencies
I'm using LibGDX 1.9.7 right now, but I believe all versions have this issue.

#### Please select the affected platforms
- [x] Windows
- [x] MacOS
Any platform with case-insensitive file system
